  "abstract": "N'Djamena (; French: N'Djaména， pronounced [n(ə)dʒa.me.na]; Arabic: انجمينا‎ Injamīnā) is the capital and largest city of Chad. A port on the Chari River， near the confluence with the Logone River， it directly faces the Cameroonian town of Kousséri， to which the city is connected by a bridge. It is also a special statute region， divided into 10 districts or arrondissements. It is a regional market for livestock， salt， dates， and grains. Meat， fish and cotton processing are the chief industries， and the city continues to serve as the center of economic activity in Chad."
