  "abstract": "Conakry (; French pronunciation: ​[kɔnakʁi]; Susu: Kɔnakiri; N’ko: ߞߐߣߊߞߙߌ߫， Fula: Konaakiri 𞤑𞤮𞤲𞤢𞥄𞤳𞤭𞤪𞤭) is the capital and largest city of Guinea. A port city， it serves as the economic， financial and cultural centre of Guinea. Its population as of the 2014 Guinea census was 1，660，973.The current population of Conakry is difficult to ascertain， although the U.S. Department of State's Bureau of African Affairs has estimated it at 2 million， accounting for one sixth of the entire population of the country."
