  "abstract": "Niamey (French pronunciation: ​[njamɛ]) is the capital and largest city of Niger.  Niamey lies on the Niger River， primarily situated on the east bank. Niamey's population was counted as 1，026，848 as of the 2012 census. As of 2017， population projections show the capital district growing at a slower rate than the country as a whole， which has the world's highest fertility rate.The city is located in a pearl millet growing region， while manufacturing industries include bricks， ceramic goods， cement and weaving."
